next
  Summary: cause/consequence architecture rationalization. Specific causes everywhere. AREA_CONQUER split into Human and Mutant. INFEST joined AREA family. Per-cause toggles on every cause. MCM tag-widget format. Personality clamp global. Framework tab.
  Gameplay:
    Changed: AREA_CONQUER is now two consequences. Human and Mutant run independently from the same cause and have their own MCM toggles.
    Changed: INFEST moved from mutant instincts to AREA family. Trigger conditions are unchanged. Cause name and rate-limit budget differ.
    Changed: stash AMBUSH now fires on-arrive. The arrival resets the opportunity DTO timestamp. There is no item action.
    Changed: instincts use scent range exclusively. Scatter detects higher-tier threats by scent (was eye range). Roam destination is any-distance scent (no minimum).
    Added: massacre_loot consequence. Outlaws (bandits, renegades, Greh) walk to massacre sites and strip corpses for weapons and gear, alongside the cowardly mutants that scavenge.
    Changed: massacre_scavenge narrowed to cowardly mutants (flesh, zombie, tushkano, rat, karlik). Outlaws no longer scavenge through this path; they loot via the new massacre_loot consequence.
    Changed: wounded_hunt narrowed to predator and aberrant mutants. Outlaws no longer hunt wounded NPCs.
    Removed: squadkill_flee consequence. Cause:squadkill now triggers only squadkill_revenge. Same-faction squads no longer flee to base after a squadwipe.
  Core:
    Changed: news pipeline owns its session FIFO. Activity record removed from broker. Each consequence rolls a chance to publish; on hit, the entry is appended with display strings eager-captured at write time.
    Changed: per-category cause budget check moved from core to ext. Each cause predicate self-gates against its own MCM cap; core's limiter is now a generic counter primitive.
    Changed: HUD reads two live registers per tick (broker scripted squads, tracker alpha squads). No internal copy, no intersection logic. Scripted wins on overlap by fill order. Marker label is two lines (action phrase, subject); the "Other:" line is dropped.
    Changed: cause-side rate limit is per-CATEGORY (REACTIONS / NEEDS / INSTINCTS / OPPORTUNITIES). Single global cap removed.
    Changed: opportunity DTO threshold gates replace wall-clock cooldowns for stash and area causes.
    Changed: stash predicate finds and classifies the stash before publishing. Cascade slots are not wasted when no stash is in range.
    Changed: every cause carries its own enable toggle. Drive-level enable cfg keys removed for needs and instincts. Multi-answer drives share only Hull threshold + DTO timestamp.
  MCM:
    Added: news_chance slider (0-100, default 20) under News tab. Chance any single consequence publishes a news entry on success.
    Added: cause_max_reactions, cause_max_needs, cause_max_instincts, cause_max_opportunities (4 sliders, default 20/60s each).
    Added: cause_stash_loot_enabled, cause_stash_ambush_enabled, cause_stash_fill_enabled (per-cause toggles).
    Added: cause_stash_loot_threshold, cause_stash_ambush_threshold, cause_stash_fill_threshold (game hours).
    Added: cause_area_conquer_enabled, cause_area_conquer_threshold, cause_area_infest_threshold (game hours).
    Added: consequence_area_conquer_human_*, consequence_area_conquer_mutant_* (replaces consequence_area_conquer_*).
    Added: consequence_stash_ambush_min_items (outlaw ambush vs loot discriminator).
    Added: sub-cause tag widgets for stash (3), area (3), needs (14), instincts (7), reactive families (7). Each radiant cause section displays its own folded Cause/Desc/Rules tag.
    Renamed: General tab -> Framework. The tab holds pipeline knobs only (alife ratio, distributor interval, category budgets, ownership flag).
    Removed: cause_max_events (replaced by 4 per-category sliders).
    Removed: cause_needs_enabled, cause_instincts_enabled, cause_stash_enabled, cause_area_enabled (master umbrella toggles). Use per-cause toggles instead.
    Removed: drive-level enable cfg keys (cause_<drive>_enabled for hunger, sleep, rest, heal, shelter, money, supply, job, social, slumber). Each answer carries its own enable.
    Removed: per-cause and per-consequence personality_min / personality_max sliders (~50 cfg keys). Global clamp lives in ap_ext_const.PERSONALITY_FLOOR / PERSONALITY_CEILING (0.10 / 0.70).
    Renamed: cause_instinct_infest_* -> cause_area_infest_*. Renamed: consequence_instinct_infest_* -> consequence_area_infest_*. Reset to defaults on first load.
    Removed: area_conquest_enabled (duplicate gate). area_conquest_mutate_smart is the single conquest mutation toggle.
    Renamed: infest_enabled / infest_max_per_level / infest_spawn_num / infest_decay_hours -> area_infest_mutate_smart / area_infest_max_per_level / area_infest_spawn_num / area_infest_decay_hours. Parity with area_conquest_*. Reset to defaults on first load.
    Moved: smart mutator settings (area_conquest_*, area_infest_*) from the area_conquer / area_infest consequence sections into the Mutators tab. Smart mutations are smart-terrain behavior, parallel to alpha and rank object mutators. Cause and consequence sections now hold squad behavior only.
    Changed: alignment text uses plain English in MCM tags. alignment_human renders as "any stalker", alignment_outlaw as "outlaw stalkers", alignment_conquer_mutant as "feral, predator, or aberrant mutants", etc. Internal alignment_* codes stay in technical docs.
    Changed: trait names are lowercase in MCM tags. personality(survival), personality(greed, perception). PERSONALITY.* enum constants in code stay uppercase.
    Added: Massacre Loot section under Consequences. Enabled toggle, rush mode, max squads slider.
    Changed: consequence pages render a single uncolored tag widget with Desc / Cause / Rules stacked. Cause references the parent cause display name. Rules appears only on reactive consequences (radiant consequences carry only Desc and Cause since the cause owns the gates). Old yellow _tag + paragraph _desc pair retired.
    Changed: needs and instincts cause pages reordered. All cause blocks first (uniform tag + enable per answer), then drive thresholds in a second block. Drive-vs-answer surfaced by page structure rather than subtitles.
    Fixed: missing menu sidebar labels rendering raw keys for massacre_loot, conquest, infest.
  Integration:
    Changed: ap_ext_news.record_event(squad, cause, consequence, opts) -> ap_ext_news.add(squad, cause, consequence, opts). Same arity. opts.cause_id dropped.
    Added: ap_ext_news.add_unfiltered(squad, cause, consequence, opts) for debug seeders that bypass news_chance.
    Removed: ap_core_broker.record / get_record / get_records / clear_record / RECORD_CAPACITY. News owns its FIFO.
    Removed: opts.cause_id and result._cause_id from cause/consequence payloads. cause_id was used only by the deleted pair pool.
    Changed: ap_core_limiter.check_cause_rate_limit signature -> (key, max). Caller supplies counter key and cap.
    Moved: CAUSE_CATEGORY enum from ap_core_const to ap_ext_const.
    Added: ap_ext_tracker.get_alpha_marker_squads() returns array of squad ids hosting alphas (for HUD identity-source registration).
    Added: ap_ext_util.get_faction_display(faction) and ap_ext_util.get_species_display(species). Lifted from ap_ext_news so HUD and news share one translation path.
    Added: ap_core_hud.register_identity_source(fn) and ap_core_hud.register_subject_resolver(fn). Ext registers at on_game_start; core has zero ext imports.
    Changed: producer.register signature is now register(config, handler). config must include callback, cause_type, category.
    Changed: ap_ext_util.check_personality opts no longer carries p_min / p_max. Floor and ceiling are read from ap_ext_const.PERSONALITY_FLOOR / PERSONALITY_CEILING.
    Added: CAUSE_CATEGORY enum (REACTIONS / NEEDS / INSTINCTS / OPPORTUNITIES) for rate-limit grouping and MCM organization.
    Added: structural rules section in architecture.md governing cause/consequence code shape (specific causes only, umbrella generators, _set files, CONFIGS factory scope, N:M mapping, toggle requirements).
    Added: synchronous payload only rule (conventions.md A-Life Rules). Server userdata in cause payloads is valid for the synchronous dispatch chain only; deferred consumers (xlice/CreateTimeEvent jobs, on_arrive callbacks, periodic scanners) must use server IDs and re-resolve.
    Added: scan tracing layered rule (conventions.md Logging). Top-level destination SCAN -> find_smart_observed / find_squads_observed; inside a nested PHASE observe -> plain (parent captures via dst_id); inside a deferred-tick fresh-trace envelope -> plain.
    Renamed: ap_core_utils -> ap_core_util (singular, matching ap_ext_util). All find_smart / find_squads / find_*_observed / event_publish / event_subscribe / get_entity_id / count_until_threshold callers must update the namespace prefix.
    Added: ap_ext_common module hosting shared ext-domain dispatch patterns. Today: chase pattern (move_actor_chasers, make_move_smart_chasers, make_on_arrive). Used internally by harvest_rob, alphakill_targeted, squadkill_revenge; available to integrators implementing similar pursuit consequences.
    Renamed: cause:massacre and cause:basekill payload field "total_deaths" / "death_count" -> "kill_count". External listeners reading the diagnostic field must update.
    Removed: cause:squadkill payload field "killer_squad". Consumers re-resolve via xobject.se(killer_squad_id) per the synchronous payload only rule. The userdata field was unused after the killer_squad_id addition.
    Removed: cause:alphakill payload fields "name", "alpha_level", "kills". Never read by AP. Subscribers that need them should resolve via xcreature.get_name(killer_id) and ap_ext_tracker.get_alpha_level(victim_id) at read time.
  Compatibility:
    Added: v1.5.5 save migration releases scripted_target on all broker squads then drops the table. Required because the INFEST consequence rename leaves stale arrival keys.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: scripted squads froze idle for the full pre_release_gulag duration when arriving at a smart with no free job slots while visible to the actor. Arrival path in ap_core_broker now checks xsmart.has_jobs_for when smart is online + on actor's level; releases the squad on failure (release_no_jobs) instead of entering the wait state.
    Fixed: stalker squad needs dispatches no longer target smarts whose stalker_jobs[] contains only generic_point and campfire_point stubs (level designer authored no walker / guard / sniper / etc. patrol paths). Seven needs filters (heal_shelter, shelter_indoor, money_harvest, money_hunt, job_outpost, job_explore, job_research) AND-compose xsmart.has_animated_stalker_jobs at scan-time; supply_trader uses xsmart.has_stalker_jobs(JOB_TYPE_TRADER). Pairs with the arrival-time has_jobs_for gate.
    Fixed: AREA_CONQUER handler crammed stalker and mutant logic in one function. They are now two distinct handlers.
    Fixed: news template pool for INFEST was orphaned after the cause rename. Templates now align with consequence:area_infest.
    Fixed: harvest_haunt and wounded_hunt no longer dispatch mutant squads with broken commander state into species-restricted consequences. Only resolved aberrant species reach harvest_haunt; only resolved predator and aberrant species reach wounded_hunt.
    Fixed: alpha kill events (cause:alphakill) no longer fire when the killer is a protected story NPC, trader, or named character. Aligns with the protection rule already applied to the alpha, wounded, and harvest causes.
    Fixed: squadkill_revenge consequence dead for NPC-vs-NPC kills since 1.5.0. Cause publisher now ships killer_squad_id; the revenge gate no longer rejects every non-player kill with NO_KILLER_SQUAD.
    Fixed: map markers stuck on the engine map after squads were unscripted. _on_first_update now removes any stale marker timer before recreating it, so re-entry on level transition or save reload no longer breaks the recurring update chain.
    Fixed: alpha_promote markers vanished 60s after the alpha's last AP scripting cycle. Per-consequence persistent flag restored on CONSEQUENCE_INFO; persistent markers skip linger and clear only on entity unregister.
  Localization:
    Removed: pair-composite news templates (25 ids per locale). News now uses per-consequence templates only.
