1.5.0
  Summary: PDA news system, mutant infestation, additive territory conquest, generative templates, localization (EN+RU), modder API, personality retune
  Gameplay:
    Added: PDA news system. An online stalker on your frequency relays squad activity as radio chatter.
           The framework records every cause and consequence in the simulation as a journal entry.
           News surfaces the journal as emergent gossip, based on how impactful the event is and how relevant the data is for the world.
           Speakers rotate across hearsay, witness, survivor, tracker, and named report.
           Speakers are chosen based on whether they were part of the event, saw the event or proximity to it.
           The news is about the causes, the consequences, or about chained events like a cause generating multiple consequences or consequences leading to other events.
           PDA system reworked around XRAY systems, integrated with existing news queue, respecting emissions, psi-storms, PDA charge, queue cap, and member-only faction channels.
           Visibility of the messages configurable in MCM: own faction, faction and allies, world.
           Rewrote all news text to adapt to the new chained events and to use the data saved in the core broker
    Added: mutant infestation. Feral, predator, and aberrant ALPHAS claim smart terrains as nests. Original spawns are replaced by the infesting species, turning the smart into a single-species lair. (per-map cap configurable in MCM)
    Changed: territory conquest is additive (was exclusive). Conquerors add their faction's spawns alongside the originals instead of replacing them. A conquest produces a mixed zone (vanilla behavior) instead of a clean factional flip.
    Changed: personality values and default ceiling retuned to be more in line with the lore
    Changed: stash fill skips squads at bases. Matches stash loot and stash ambush behavior.
  Core:
    Added: spawn attribution tracing. Every squad spawned by area_conquer or instinct_infest logs with smart, faction, and section when DEBUG is on.
    Added: activity records capture translated display strings for faction, name, and species (subject and other) at write time.
    Changed: All stash causes avoid bases for balance
    Changed: PDA map markers now use a multi-line label with action phrase, "Subject: name (faction)", and "Other: name (faction)" for two-party consequences.
             Markers read pre-translated fields directly from the activity record, so no string resolution at render time.
  MCM:
    Added: News tab. Master toggle, compose interval (1-600 seconds, default 30-100). Scope selector (own / allies / world, default allies). Max age (1-72 game hours, default 12).
    Added: instinct infest settings. Enabled, threshold, rush, personality floor and ceiling.
    Added: infestation mutator settings. Enabled, max per level, spawn count, decay hours.
    Removed: per-consequence PDA chance sliders. News volume is tuned from the News tab.
  Integration:
    Added: activity record API (ap_core_broker).
           record(squad_id, cause, consequence, opts) - write a record
           get_record(opts) - O(1) read for { squad_id, assigned = true }
           get_records(opts) - bulk read
           clear_record(squad_id) - unregister from all systems on entity death
    Added: localized rendering (ap_core_const.CONSEQUENCE_INFO).
           CONSEQUENCE_INFO[consequence] returns { name_key, action_key }
           name_key - short caption ("Massacre Investigate")
           action_key - full action phrase ("Investigating a Massacre Site")
           Both XML ids resolve via game.translate_string. EN and RU ship.
    Added: trace paths.
           ap_core_const.CONSEQUENCE_PHASE - sub-phase identifiers (FIND_TARGETS, MOVE_SQUAD, ARRIVE, etc.)
           ap_core_debug.observe consumes them at DEBUG log level.
    Added: news dispatch (ap_ext_news).
           record_event(subject_squad, cause, consequence, opts) - main entry
           opts.cause_id - groups siblings for paired dispatch
           opts.other_squad - enables two-party templates
           Template pools follow per-consequence, paired, and pattern id conventions.
    Added: spawn injection (xsmart).
           set_shared_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) - alongside originals (conquest pattern)
           set_exclusive_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) - replaces originals (infest pattern)
           Identity accepts stalker factions and mutant species.
    Added: xlibs helpers used by AP.
           xsquad.get_commander_name - commander character_name
           xcreature.get_mutant_species - cached species detection
           xlevel.get_level_name - localized level name from level_id
           xstring.capitalize_first - cp1251-aware first-char uppercase
           xttltable fifo_cache :each + on_evict - bounded cache traversal and eviction hook

  Fixes:
    Fixed: squadkill_revenge chased the player after the player's actor_stalker relation drifted hostile from own-faction kills.
    Fixed: better discovering of player and NPC true community when dispathcing news
    Fixed: Russian MCM News tab strings synced with English.

1.4.0
  Summary: Mutant instincts, pipeline redesign, day/night cycle, food chain, range-based perception, personality recalibration, statistics overlay, integration API
  Gameplay:
    Added: mutant instincts. Five deprivation-scored drives (scatter, feed, sleep, explore, socialize) parallel to stalker needs. Per-instinct xbus routing, Hull drive competition, independent thresholds.
    Changed: mutant personality and alignment redesigned from GSC source (monstry.doc). Species and subspecies detection via xlibs replaces naive community categories.
    Added: food chain. Four behavioral groups (cowardly, feral, predator, aberrant) with tiered avoidance. Cowardly flees feral+predator+aberrant, feral flees predator+aberrant, predator flees aberrant.
    Added: day/night cycle. Stalkers work by day, rest at night. Nocturnal mutants (bloodsuckers, lurkers, chimeras, zombies, fractures) hunt at night, retreat at dawn. All needs and instincts time-gated accordingly.
    Added: range-based perception. EyeRange (200m, vision), RadioRange (500m, stalker PDA), ScentRange (500m, mutant tracking). Each cause type maps to a range tier. Distances derived from empirical smart terrain geometry analysis across 14 levels (nearest-neighbor spacing, vertex density, level dimensions).
    Changed: when an alpha dies, same-species mutants on the level hunt the killer.
    Added: artefact pickup triggers reactions. Outlaws chase the taker. Aberrant mutants converge on the site.
    Changed: decay and cooldown timers use game time (respects time acceleration and realism mods).
  Core:
    Changed: pipeline redesign. Ineligible squads filtered before evaluation budget. Every trigger produces a result.
    Changed: cascading causes with pure predicate gates. Rejections skip expensive queries and immediately try the next cause.
    Added: squad ownership reassertion. Dead squad cleanup. Invalid cause-consequence pairs blocked at cause level.
    Added: statistics overlay. Real-time pipeline metrics (rates, blockers, counts), configurable position via MCM.
    Changed: map markers use blue icons, linger 60s after completion, then fade.
    Changed: general tuning (rush defaults, gulag duration, return-to-simulation timing).
  MCM:
    Added: instincts configuration. Per-instinct toggles, thresholds, and rush settings.
    Added: statistics overlay configuration.
    Added: per-consequence personality floor and ceiling sliders.
  Integration:
    Added: activity record API. record() and get_record() for external mods (e.g. warfare map tooltips).
    Added: PDA marker descriptions via register_descriptions().
    Changed: register_owner() supports override. Integration guide rewritten with current API and examples.
  Compatibility:
    Removed: modded exes requirement. Works with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3, Demonized, Demonized MT, AOEngine. Tested with GAMMA, EFP, Zona.

1.3.6
  Summary: Hotfix, save compat
  Fixed: updated save migrations. Old scripted squad entries released and rebuilt on load.

1.3.5
  Summary: Alignment system, alpha mutants, reactive chaining, combat mutators, expanded mutant factions
  Gameplay:
    Added: alpha mutants. Mutants that rack up kills become alphas. They hit harder, absorb more punishment, never flee, and drop bonus loot for their species. Scales with kill level. Each feature toggleable in MCM.
    Added: alpha kill retaliation. Killing an alpha triggers same-species mutants to hunt the killer.
    Added: species-based squad death responses. Predator and territorial packs avenge killed members. Herbivores and weak mobs scatter.
    Added: combat mutators via hit callbacks. Alpha hit power scales with kill level. Veteran+ stalker hit power scales from veteran to legend rank. Separate MCM toggles.
    Added: alignment system based on GSC's moral axis (principled, self-serving, unprincipled, outlaw). Military never flees, ecologists never conquer, renegades never investigate etc
    Added: mutant territorial behavior. Mutants conquer territory, avenge their dead, and hunt wounded stalkers based on personality traits.
    Changed: reactive consequences chain. A single event now triggers multiple independent responses. A squad wipe fires both revenge and retreat. A medkit use attracts predators and sends allies to help. A massacre draws scavengers and investigators.
    Changed: personality probability narrowed. Factions commit to identity-consistent behavior more often and hesitate less.
    Changed: squads stay at destinations for realistic durations to let gulag jobs (patrol, sleep, socialize etc) unfold. Previously all squads left after 5 minutes.
    Removed: stalker elites. The engine tracks stalker progression natively through kill-to-rank points.
    Removed: elite kill bounty.
  Core:
    Added: mutators MCM section with toggles for alpha and stalker combat modifiers.
    Added: tracing statistics every minute when debug is on, will help standardise log parsing from users
  i18n:
    Added: full Russian description (doc/readme_ru.txt).
    Fixed: Russian MCM synced with English.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: crash on fast travel when a scripted squad dies offline and the engine recycles its entity ID.

1.3.0
  Summary: Personality system, mutant conquest, territory decay, round-robin dispatch, ownership registry, integration framework, fixes
  Requires xlibs update.

  Gameplay:
    Added: personality profiles for all stalker and mutant factions with trait-driven consequence selection.
    Added: persistent map markers for elite promotion. Marks the elite's squad on the PDA until death.
    Added: squad ownership registry. Alife mods register an ownership filter, AlifePlus skips squads they own. Warfare and BAO registered via legacy proxies.
    Added: integration API for external mods. Register custom causes and consequences without modifying AlifePlus code.
    Added: automatic save data cleanup on version upgrade. Orphaned squads released, stale keys removed.
    Added: conquered territory decays after configurable game hours if not reconquered.
    Added: per-smart cooldown on area cause. Same location cannot trigger conquest repeatedly.
    Changed: each needs consequence tied to specific personality traits. Hunger and sleep use survival, money uses greed, jobs use territory and perception, social uses relation.
    Changed: per-consequence rate budget tightened. The same consequence type cannot dominate a session.
    Changed: post-arrival wait uses game time. Advances during time skips, survives save and load.
    Changed: squads detected as arrived faster (scan interval reduced).
    Changed: stash consequences (loot, ambush, fill) harmonized into the same config-driven pattern as needs.
    Changed: smart terrain mutation and load restore unified into a single periodic update.
    Changed: radiant interval and global consequence budget defaults adjusted for less frequent, more varied activity.
    Removed: job_worship and job_exercise consequences, MCM entries, PDA messages, and item sections.
    Removed: per-consequence chance sliders. Replaced by personality system. PDA chance sliders remain.
  Compatibility:
    Fixed: warfare and BAO ownership filters gave false positives on squads without the expected field.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: area conquest MCM toggle had no effect on previously conquered smart terrains.
    Fixed: radiant causes did not fire on first session after game start.
    Fixed: needs thresholds broke on young saves with low game time.
  Internal:
    Changed: codebase restructured into core (pipeline) and ext (domain).
    Changed: chance gate removal eliminates per-consequence random rolls from every dispatch cycle.
    Changed: protection gate no longer allocates strings below DEBUG log level.
    Changed: producer luabind crossings reduced via global xlibs caching.
    Changed: pacer retries faster on protection reject instead of burning the full interval.
    Changed: radiant and reactive pipelines use independent Bresenham counters. Reactive events no longer biased by radiant traffic volume.
    Added: consumer statistics (PIPELINE, CAUSES, DISPATCH, LIFECYCLE) logged every 60s at DEBUG. Zero cost above DEBUG.
    Changed: alignment and personality checks moved from core consumer to ap_ext_util. Core pipeline has zero domain knowledge.
    Changed: PDA sender selection and message dispatch moved from core to ap_ext_news. Core has zero ext references.
    Changed: all consequence gates (alignment, personality) run inside observe() with full tid/path tracing.
    Changed: guard clause detector recognizes multi-line guards and counts guards throughout the function body.
    Changed: rate limiting reworked with sliding window counters and per-pipeline pacing.
  xlibs (requires xlibs update):
    Added: composite squad protection guard with shared commander context.
    Added: vertex-to-level cache with zero luabind on repeat lookups.
    Changed: scripted check uses engine fields only. Mod-specific fields handled by AP ownership registry.
    Removed: dead code in squad and smart terrain modules.

